ransmissible spongiform encephalopathies, or prion
diseases, are a group of intriguing neurodegenerative disorders that
include scrapie in sheep and goat, bovine spongiform encephalopathy in cattle, chronic waste disorder in deer and elk, and Creutzfeldt-Jacob disease in humans (1). These diseases are associated with
conformational conversion of a normal prion protein,
PrPC,1 into a
misfolded isoform, PrPSc
